<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-746-637  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 746 637.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Design  June 22 1989 v36 n13 p29(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>1-Gbyte, 5-1/4-in. drive spins platters at 5400 RPM. (fromImprimis Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bursky, Dave.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Imprimis has pioneered the fastest 5.25-inch hard drive yet with a1Gbyte capacity.andP;  Data is read from the disk at 24-MHz and latencytime is cut to 5.56 milliseconds (ms).andP;  A new actuator designgives the unit an average seek time of just 12-ms.andP;  Thenecessarily high rotational speeds of the unit's 10 platters,spinning at 5,400 RPM, produced an excess of heat which caused aredesign of the spindle configuration.andP;  Once completed, therapidly spinning platters produced a smoother airflow thanexpected which in turn improved the dynamic movement of the headsover the media.andP;  The improved servo system also improvestrack-to-track stability.andP;  The company hopes to have samplequantities of the drive available in the fourth quarter, 1989.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Imprimis Technology Inc. (product development).andO;Topic:     Hard DiskDisk DrivesProduct DevelopmentDesignPrototype.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>